1
00:00:03,010 --> 00:00:05,720
<i>Ok Taecyeon</i>

2
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:11,250
<i>Kim Hye Yoon</i>

3
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:17,650
<i></i>

4
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:20,100
<i>Secret Royal Inspector &amp; Joy</i>

5
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:25,100
<i>The characters, organizations, geographic regions, and incidents are irrelevant to historical facts and are fiction</i>

6
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:29,050
<i>Episode 2</i> <br> <i>Butterfly: Proof of Divorce for Citizens of the Joseon Era</i>

7
00:00:33,770 --> 00:00:38,750
<i>Park Moo Gyeong. I made sure that we took care of this along with the sunken vessel.</i>

8
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:41,530
My Lord, since there is the ledger,

9
00:00:41,530 --> 00:00:44,920
don't you think things could work out as long as we get rid of the corpse?

10
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:47,350
That...

11
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:51,270
My lord, you must be aware of where it is hidden. The location, yes?

12
00:00:51,270 --> 00:00:56,620
Well, I had no time... I didn't get to find out.

13
00:00:56,620 --> 00:00:58,130
What?

14
00:01:01,860 --> 00:01:05,910
<i>Where is the ledger? Where is it!</i>

15
00:01:08,350 --> 00:01:11,650
My goodnes! Hurry up!

16
00:01:11,650 --> 00:01:14,530
This way!

17
00:01:19,710 --> 00:01:21,710
Hurry up.

18
00:01:22,540 --> 00:01:24,390
Goodness!

19
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,100
Move out of the way!

20
00:01:27,710 --> 00:01:30,490
Lower your gaze!

21
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:59,820
My lord, did you see? Just now, from the corpse...

22
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:01,630
It was a horse pass. <i>(Issued to officials dispatched out of the capital allowing use of horses from the transportation posts)</i>

23
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:05,340
If he has a horse pass, does it mean that he was also...

24
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:10,200
He must be one of the secret inspectors who was dispatched but ended up reported dead or missing.

25
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:13,220
Inspector Park Moo Gyeong went to Chungcheong Province.

26
00:02:13,220 --> 00:02:17,610
There's still no news of whether he's dead or alive.

27
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:19,770
- Yook Chil. <br>- Yes?

28
00:02:19,770 --> 00:02:23,300
- You're going to have to wear those clothes properly. <br>- What?

29
00:02:34,390 --> 00:02:36,920
Come on out!

30
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:41,680
Come on out!

31
00:02:44,050 --> 00:02:46,260
Come on--

32
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:49,980
Everyone has returned back to their homes.

33
00:02:49,980 --> 00:02:53,950
Who is making such a ruckus at our entrance?

34
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,670
Pay your respects.

35
00:02:57,670 --> 00:02:59,740
- What? <br> - If I were to introduce myself,

36
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:02,190
- I am the Chief Clown of Land and Property at Hanseongbu, the Capital Bureau. <br>- Chief Clerk.

37
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:07,060
I am the Chief Clerk. My name is Oh Dong Yoo.

38
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:09,370
As in empress tree leaves?

39
00:03:13,050 --> 00:03:17,800
That's right. The thing is, I was on my way to my hometown for a vacation.

40
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:24,040
But I ended up getting robbed by a group of thieves up on the hill.

41
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:26,490
Because of this, I have come to ask the magistrate if he could serve me gukbap <i>(rice soup)</i> and let me rest here for a bit.

42
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:32,090
I was wondering if I could seek food and shelter for the time being. That's why I'm here.

43
00:03:32,090 --> 00:03:38,260
I doubt that. Why not ask for food at a restaurant or any house?

44
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:40,830
This is a government office where important matters take place.

45
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:47,070
You fool! How could a noble man like me ask for a meal where others can see?

46
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:54,030
Yes... I do apologize, but we are in the middle of resolving urgent affairs so...

47
00:03:55,130 --> 00:04:00,730
My master is the Saheonbu's Lord Oh's first cousin once removed. <i>(Saheonbu is the Office of the Inspector-General)</i>

48
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:07,940
Bang Deuk, you fool. How dare you mention that my uncle is Lord Oh of Saheonbu?

49
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:13,300
If I have to call out a relative's name to get food in my stomach...

50
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:15,970
Then I'll look like such a desperate person.

51
00:04:15,970 --> 00:04:19,890
Now, how am I to face my uncle who is Saheonbu's Lord Oh?

52
00:04:19,890 --> 00:04:22,870
Forget that my distant uncle is Lord Oh of Saheonbu.

53
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:26,120
No, my lord. Where are you trying to go with that bad knee of yours?

54
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:32,190
If your uncle, Lord Oh of Saheonbu finds out of this, imagine how furious he'll be.

55
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:36,500
Did we struggle to walk all the way over here for our efforts to be wasted? Hurry and talk to him again.

56
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:39,430
Stop, stop, stop with it all!

57
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:45,620
If I were to die on the roadside, let that be the fate of the Chief Clerk from Hanseongbu.

58
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:47,490
Don't worry about it.

59
00:04:47,490 --> 00:04:50,330
My lord, please.

60
00:04:50,330 --> 00:04:52,390
My lord, my lord. That wasn't what I meant.

61
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:55,290
Let's go. Let's get started.

62
00:04:55,290 --> 00:05:00,980
Let's hurry on so that I can see my uncle who happens to be Lord Oh of Saheonbu.

63
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,270
Get moving, knees!

64
00:05:06,590 --> 00:05:12,360
M-m-m-y l-l-l-l-ord! Hold on. Could you wait just a moment?

65
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:26,540
- I'm telling the truth! <br>- How am I supposed to believe that?

66
00:05:26,540 --> 00:05:30,770
There have been more than one case of fraudsters claiming to have powerful relatives.

67
00:05:30,770 --> 00:05:36,060
What if we send him back, but it turns out to be the truth? Then what will we do?

68
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:40,220
Even so, we cannot let just anyone in here in the midst of this chaos.

69
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:45,040
Why don't we just fix him a bowl of rice soup and send him on his way?

70
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:48,390
Are you willing to risk your honor for a measly bowl of rice?

71
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:57,220
In the meantime, I will go and search for the ledger.

72
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:01,960
- Where is the book? <br> - I told you, I don't know!

73
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:06,390
Bo Ri must have gone and hidden it well somewhere.

74
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:15,190
So you must definitely find it and bring it back. You must.

75
00:06:15,190 --> 00:06:19,760
Hurry, hurry. Go on.

76
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:23,420
<i>It is Bo Ri.</i>

77
00:06:51,330 --> 00:06:53,360
Rotten girl.

78
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:59,990
<i>Unni, you're going to organize everything for me, right?</i>

79
00:07:00,740 --> 00:07:04,730
I don't know. Why do I have to look after you anyway?

80
00:07:04,730 --> 00:07:07,730
<i>Besides you, Unni, I don't have any family.</i>

81
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:10,400
Again, again! With those words of yours.

82
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:14,330
Then why did you have to die before your time?

83
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:18,610
<i>You're going to do everything anyway, but you always act like this.</i>

84
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:25,080
<i>Unni, make sure to clean everything here.</i>

85
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:30,800
<i>And my belongings... Burn them thoroughly, so they can be sent off with me.</i>

86
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:34,160
<i>Understand?</i>

87
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:39,160
You're funny. Fool.

88
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:08,840
She couldn't even put this tiny jeogori (<i>Traditional jacket</i>) on them.

89
00:08:18,530 --> 00:08:23,360
You were always sweet and never enjoyed life.

90
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:26,670
You were amazing, Hwang Bo Ri.

91
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:30,830
You stupid half-witted fool, so completely dumb.

92
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:38,590
Even if it's just this.

93
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:42,790
I'll make sure to bury this well. I'll make sure of it, Bo Ri.

94
00:09:00,690 --> 00:09:04,920
<i>It's Bo Ri.</i>

95
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:23,420
Ah, why is that girl in a room without its owner?

96
00:09:23,420 --> 00:09:25,400
What if she finds the book?

97
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:29,180
Ah no, even if she did find it, she'd have no idea what it was. Then should I go in and drive her out?

98
00:09:29,180 --> 00:09:33,050
No, no. That'll garner more suspicion.

99
00:09:33,050 --> 00:09:35,220
Ah, my lord.

100
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:42,340
Have you seen my daughter-in-law by chance?

101
00:09:42,340 --> 00:09:46,580
That wench ran away through the back entrance again.

102
00:09:46,580 --> 00:09:50,790
I felt anxious about it so I left it open and worked around it.

103
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:53,590
I don't really want to hear that story with all those specifics.

104
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:57,730
Ah, that wench. That wench has gone to Bo Ri's again.

105
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:08,000
Let her be alone. She's grieving over a lost friend.

106
00:10:11,230 --> 00:10:15,260
Have you eaten... dinner yet?

107
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:25,040
If not, would you like to come over to my house

108
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:30,430
and have some dinner while listening to my story?

109
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:35,500
I'm so frustrated that I don't think I can live.

110
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:39,770
I'm... not... hungry.

111
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:51,190
Then why are you, this late at night,

112
00:10:51,190 --> 00:10:56,900
wandering around the tavern like you're looking for something?

113
00:10:56,900 --> 00:11:00,050
A widow knows what widower's situation.

114
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:04,920
Even if you went back home, you'd be lonely.

115
00:11:06,890 --> 00:11:10,100
This person...

116
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:15,750
By the way, what were you doing at that wench Bo Ri's?

117
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:18,430
Well. Let's go, let's go. Let's go home and talk.

118
00:11:18,430 --> 00:11:21,340
Then were you two in some kind of relationship?

119
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:23,910
Let's hurry and go.

120
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:32,920
Welcome, Your Excellency.

121
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:38,450
When I see him running and playing with a bell hanging under his chin, I'm not aware the time for sales has passed.

122
00:11:38,450 --> 00:11:41,660
- Please give me the price of one pear... <br> - Are you out of white doves?

123
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:48,240
White doves are so scarce you have to get them from a merchant in Nagasaki, Japan.

124
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:51,330
They are worth a set of dear antlers.

125
00:11:51,330 --> 00:11:54,250
If you obtain one for me, I'll give you two sets of deer antlers.

126
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,810
Yes, I will. Yes.

127
00:11:56,810 --> 00:11:59,850
The makkuraji* <i> *Mud fish, loach, "rotten apple", "sneaky person"</i>

128
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:04,500
This is a place which sells mudfish as food for cranes.

129
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,870
I came here for that.

130
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:09,570
Did you go through the effort of coming all the way here to buy mudfish?

131
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:14,590
Our household's crane caught and ate all the bugs and worms.

132
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:18,580
I heard the news that you have slippery guys.

133
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:23,190
Please be careful. If you get caught by a crane, it's all over.

134
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:31,240
Do you think you will become a crane yourself? (<i>Joseon official wore robes with cranes embroidered on them</i>)

135
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:34,060
In my view, you and I are mudfish.

136
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:36,790
In front of the crane called His Majesty the King.

137
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:43,120
I raised a crane and when the feathers I cut grew back, it flew away.

138
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:48,630
Don't be so sure how long the State Councillor will remain in your mockery.

139
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:54,080
Even if my crane were to fly away, how will it go to you?

140
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:59,120
Hurry and purchase the mudfish and feed your crane.

141
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:03,090
Have a safe trip, Your Excellency.

142
00:13:07,220 --> 00:13:12,000
I can't believe he couldn't handle anything properly.

143
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:15,300
Where on earth is Tae So and what is he doing?

144
00:14:06,990 --> 00:14:09,480
Tae So, Tae So, you came here.

145
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:12,240
What is the Head of Shipping doing here so late at night?

146
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:16,590
- That's what I mean. <br> - I came at the right time.

147
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:21,430
Take a look at this. It's silver.

148
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,880
Yes.

149
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:27,500
You finally succeeded in separating the silver from the silver ore.

150
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:31,970
What did I say? Didn't I say I could do it?

151
00:14:31,970 --> 00:14:34,890
From one geun (<i>a Korean measure of weight</i>) of silver ore, I will get two silver coins.

152
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:38,550
Now we will be able to trade with countries which used silver as currency.

153
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:41,220
We must buy weapons.

154
00:14:41,220 --> 00:14:44,650
It's enough to overthrow Joseon.

155
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:50,500
F-for th-that, c-c-congratulations. But, this isn't the time for that.

156
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:54,610
Oh, gosh. We can't find the ledger.

157
00:14:54,610 --> 00:14:58,480
I found the concubine of the magistrate, according to what the secretary said.

158
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:03,670
She never opened her mouth. I tried to intimidate her and she fell to the bottom of the valley.

159
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,900
What is the Chief State Councillor doing?

160
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:11,160
Another royal inspector was dispatched from Hanyang.

161
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:16,960
You should have said to search the Flower Valley even if it was all burned down.

162
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:29,800
Whether you rip it or flay it to death, His Excellency will take care of it.

163
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,900
Whether it is a magistrate or a royal inspector, it doesn't matter.

164
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:37,550
What we need is the ledger. Do you understand?

165
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:42,990
I know it is the ledger. The ledger.

166
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:50,100
Gracious. Thank you for your hospitality.

167
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:55,790
This, this, this. These days I have hand tremors.

168
00:15:55,790 --> 00:16:00,640
If it's not disrespectful, could I ask my assistant for some help.

169
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:03,160
Of course.

170
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:05,060
I appreciate that.

171
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:10,570
Bang Deuk, come here and serve me.

172
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:20,360
Kneel. Kneel.

173
00:16:23,540 --> 00:16:26,250
Water. Give me some water.

174
00:16:27,110 --> 00:16:28,660
Yes, sir.

175
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:38,820
<i>If he is truly the nephew of the inspector general, why, of all places, is he here now?</i>

176
00:16:38,820 --> 00:16:41,930
<i>Young Master, please spare me. Do I really have to do this?</i>

177
00:16:41,930 --> 00:16:44,320
<i>Start.</i>

178
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:47,360
<i>You are so mean.</i> <br> Oh, by the way.

179
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:51,790
On my way here earlier, I happened to see someone dead.

180
00:16:51,790 --> 00:16:57,190
Dead, you say? Who? Jeez. No way.

181
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:59,890
But why are you so surprised?

182
00:16:59,890 --> 00:17:02,360
She was a woman from this village.

183
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:06,890
Oh, a woman. That's right.

184
00:17:06,890 --> 00:17:12,480
It seems she lost her footing after going up the mountain to bathe.

185
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:15,730
The terrain around this village is rough.

186
00:17:15,730 --> 00:17:20,440
Well, we are discussing how to prevent such unfortunate accidents.

187
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,400
You've worked too hard today.

188
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:28,660
<i>More meat jun. Hurry up.</i>

189
00:17:28,660 --> 00:17:30,490
<i>Bite it.</i>

190
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:38,450
I mean... I am, well, when it comes to criminal matters, I am an outsider.

191
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:44,690
Ordinarily, when there is a death, don't you examine the body?

192
00:17:46,490 --> 00:17:49,970
It isn't a murder case, so how can I do an examination of the body?

193
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:53,330
That woman died accidentally.

194
00:17:54,770 --> 00:17:58,530
I see. I didn't know.

195
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:03,230
Not at all. That can happen when you don't know.

196
00:18:03,230 --> 00:18:07,200
She was someone who was skilled in cooking.

197
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:14,570
<i>Dig deeper.</i>

198
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:19,820
But there's something a bit strange.

199
00:18:19,820 --> 00:18:23,830
A woman with child went to take a bath in a cold valley stream.

200
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:30,490
Furthermore, I wonder how she climbed to the top of the mountain with her pregnant body.

201
00:18:31,530 --> 00:18:37,100
But how do you know she was pregnant?

202
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:43,830
Well, that, I heard people whispering outside the front of the government office.

203
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:48,440
But how do you know that?

204
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:56,060
Oh? I, too, hear this and that around the village.

205
00:18:58,130 --> 00:19:02,180
It seems there isn't a husband. Tsk, tsk, tsk.

206
00:19:04,370 --> 00:19:10,290
